Everything about this app is amazing, but on this review I wanted to put more emphasis into a specific feature: the frame delay. I personally think this feature is pure genius and has help me very much in animation. This has especially helped me in parts of my anims that have dialogue. instead of spamming the add frame button and hoping that it is long enough for people to read and not too long, now I can just use this feature. It saved much of my time and storage. Thank you for this solid app!
replyContent: Frame delay is honestly one of most underused great features, but, I think so probably differently from you. Having 1 frame delay for "10 seconds" (to display text, for example) vs spamming 100 frames for the same effect = MASSIVE memory saving. Combine with the Movieclip trick for backgrounds = more memory saving. Thanks 4 rating!

I would prefer a toolbar approach with pop-up guidance notes to what I find a cluttered toolbox, even with its quick 'section selection' system. It isn't obvious to me how some of the more advanced features work and I can't find any tutorials or manual to explain them. Comprehensive and clear instruction could help so much in accessing the potential of this app which I would otherwise give 5*
replyContent: Thanks for the review and ideas! Clutter is one of the biggest struggles I have with the app, and I'm constantly battling it to keep things as "simple" as possible. (There is a "Quick Menu" option you can turn on in "App Settings", might help you bounce around from menu to menu easier). Plus I rly need to make a "basic" tutorial to help new users.
